  The former governor also condemned the mysterious fire that gutted the secretariat of the Kaduna State Independent Electoral Commission (KADSIECOM) yesterday, in which the entire secretariat was completely razed down, one month to the conduct of Council polls in the State. Documents and recently acquired electronic voting machines meant for the council polls scheduled for May 12, 2019 in all the 23 local government councils might have been destroyed. The fire was said to have started around 10. 45 am, but as at 11:24am when The Guardian visited the top floor was still in flames, even as fire fighters were seen struggling to put out the inferno with more trucks from the state fire fighting unit driving in. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .